trend_summary: Across the series the area shifts from patchy development to a more continuous fabric. Housing infill spreads west and south, and several new commercial blocks line the main corridor. Forest margins shrink, roads are widened and more parking is paved, indicating gradual but sustained suburban consolidation.
notable_changes: Construction of multiple office/retail complexes along the central east-west arterial.
South-western subdivision built out with noticeably more residential rooftops.
Southern highway widened and fitted with additional ramps/lanes.
Growth of large parking lots and other impervious surfaces around industrial/commercial sites.
Incremental loss of tree cover, especially at forest edges near new developments.
